Package: GeoLightViz
Title: Interactive Visualization Tool for Light-Level Geolocator Analysis
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("RaphaÃ«l", "Nussbaumer", , "rafnuss@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8185-1020"))
Description: Provides an interactive Shiny application for exploring and 
    understanding light-level geolocator data analysis. The app features a 
    unique side-by-side visualization that shows how twilight events 
    (sunrise/sunset times) translate to geographic positions on a map in 
    real-time. Users can interactively label twilight data, define stationary 
    periods, test position hypotheses by clicking on the map, and explore 
    calibration effects and likelihood surfaces. Designed to make the complex 
    twilight geolocation method more transparent and intuitive, helping 
    researchers understand data quality, position uncertainty, and the role 
    of calibration in improving estimates.
